Well, QS has letters for diphthongs, which are arguably two sounds.
Personally I think it&#39;s perfectly clear to user #36+25 for NURSE,
whether displayed as a ligature or simply two letters quite close
together. I don&#39;t see why we would need to consider the ligature to be
a separate letter.

My dictionary defines a phoneme as &quot;any of the perceptually distinct
unit of sound in a specified language that distinguish one word from
another&quot;. Call me crazy, but I think I can perceive two units of
sounds in /3r/.

I would be interested to know more about how Read&#39;s thinking evolved
as he proceeded from Shavian to Quickscript. The fact is, he didn&#39;t
assign /3r/ to a single letter.

And by all means, Paul--take a break and ignore feature requests from
the rest of us when you&#39;re too busy! Thanks for everything you&#39;re
doing.

Ted


